  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nAll Bellatrix blocks before TTD contain a 0x0 fee recipient and will fail the equality check done by `--strict-fee-recipient` here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/aa022f46855df2a1420a6a80a788c73dc2779aa7/validator_client/src/block_service.rs#L380-L389\r\n\r\nThis is checked for both blinded and full blocks, so the fallback from blinded to full doesn't save us.\r\n\r\nWe should check that the payload is non-default before enforcing the check. Alternatively we could remove references to `--strict-fee-recipient` from the docs and deprecate the flag seeing as it's unlikely to be useful when builders are used.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nv3.1.0",
